news.title: A balance budget with some hits and some misses, says real estate industry stakeholders
news.para: From the real estate industry's point of view, there were no major direct announcements in the Union Budget 2023. However, industry stakeholders are still calling it a balanced budget which will help push country's economy in the right direction.

news.title: What real estate industry gained from Budget 2023
news.para: Real estate industry received some push from the Union Budget 2023. Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman announced some key initiatives and schemes in the budget that are expected to benefit real estate industry. Take a look!

news.title: Public sand mining sites to be declared in Punjab: Mining minister
news.para: Mining and geology minister Gurmeet Singh Meet Hayer said on Monday that the public mining sites will help in checking any malpractice to jack up the prices of sand and give the freedom of choice to people to buy sand from the source of choice and at price of choice.

news.title: Chhattisgarh consumer forum asks Sunita Developers to pay compensation to flat buyer
news.para: Complanint Sanjana Agrawal, a resident of Durg, had entered into an agreement with Sunita Developers in 2014 to buy a flat on the fourth floor of the multi-storey Sunita Park Phase-1 project and made the payment of Rs 57,75,729. In addition, the builder took Rs 3,00,000 for providing parking and other facilities.

news.title: Builder arrested for defrauding 200 flat buyers in Lucknow
news.para: The accused identified as Pankaj Thakur was arrested from his office. SHO, Vibhutikhand, Ram Singh, said Pankaj was working along with one Shashank Gupta and had floated a firm which used to promise flats, houses.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC orders Bhopal collector to recover RERA fine or face action
news.para: The petitioner Sanjay Sahai, a Bhopal based professor, pleaded he had bought 2400 square feet land from a builder in 2011 for Rs 8.40 lakh. Sahai paid the builder Rs 6.40 lakh but work on project didn't start till 2014.

news.title: Budget 2023 real estate: Builders expects deduction in home loans rates
news.para: Real estate industry experts say there should be some tax concessions for first-time homebuyers and re-introducing GST with an input tax credit for under-construction properties that will generate demand among homebuyers.

news.title: Real estate industry hopes for a stimulus from Budget 2023
news.para: Real estate industry grew significantly over the year 2022 despite all previous forebodings. Forecasts by some research firms state that this growth will continue in 2023. Industry stakeholders expects that Budget 2023 brings in much needed stimulus for tax payers and industry alike.

news.title: Budget 2023: Affordable housing needs boost, says Anarock
news.para: ANAROCK's Consumer Sentiment Survey finds that in 2022, demand for affordable housing has sunk precariously. In 2018, approx. 39% property seekers in the top 7 Indian cities were keen on affordable homes priced within Rs 40 lakh. This demand shrunk to its lowest levels in 2022, with just 26% property seekers looking to buy in this budget segment.

news.title: Sundaram Home Finance posts 51% growth in net profit in Q3 FY23
news.para: The home financier’s disbursements for the October-December quarter in FY23 also shot up by 51% at 985.9 crore when compared to the same quarter in FY22 at 651.8 crore, a statement here on Tuesday said.

news.title: Enforcement directorate raids SREI properties
news.para: ​The central agency's officials raided an office of the promoters at Alipore area of the city, besides at Tangra, Hastings and an upmarket residence at Anandapur allegedly belonging to officers of the organisation, he said.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to look into 2,194 applications for khata certificate from Feb 3-5
news.para: The agency is yet to check 389 applications for khata certificates in the east zone, 326 applications in the east zone, 317 in the south zone, 302 in RR Nagar, 302 in Yelahanka, 125 in Bommanahalli, and 124 in Dasarahalli. There are 2,194 applications pending.

news.title: Karnataka government to simplify real estate rules for poor
news.para: The government will also make land available to beneficiaries at concessional rates. Even purchase of land for residential purposes and construction of houses will be simplified.”

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai city up 7% to 8,694 units in January: Knight Frank
news.para: Property consultant Knight Frank India said that Mumbai city (area under BMC jurisdiction) saw property sales registration of 8,694 units in January 2023, contributing over Rs 658 crore to the state revenues.

news.title: Greater Noida authority auctions three land parcels for Rs 305 crore for residential development
news.para: The third land parcel, spread in 14,998 square metre, has been acquired by a consortium of Savana Builders Company Ltd (70%) and Eldeco Infrastructure & Property Ltd for Rs 53.01 crore against the reserve price of Rs 52.49 crore.
